<TEXT>
a landslide on a seaside road in western japan 
crushed a bus carrying vacationers home from a hot springs resort 
killing all 15 people aboard police said today 
rescuers today recovered the last seven bodies from the bus 
which was buried by large rocks and dirt from an overhanging cliff 
saturday afternoon police in fukui prefecture said 
the bus was traveling along the coast of the sea of japan 200 
miles west of tokyo fukui prefectural police spokesman noboru 
tsujioka said 
an estimated 1500 tons of rocks and dirt 100 feet high and 175 
feet wide fell into the road crushing a 3footthick concrete 
protection ledge and smothering the bus tsujioka said 
he said police believed the landslide was triggered by recent 
heavy rains 
</TEXT>
