doesnt pass likely wont take place shane said because investors 
will back out 
but shane acknowledged growing concern in the department about 
foreign investments in us airlines the department last week sent 
a letter to checchi asking several questions about the degree of 
foreign involvement in his plans to take over northwest 
the law limits foreign ownership of airlines to 25 percent and 
does not allow more than onethird of the board membership to be 
foreigners 
but shane said control not share of ownership is the critical 
issue 
