children who werent alive when man first landed 
on the moon got a chance to guide another spacecraft to a lunar 
landing monday at the challenger centers mock mission control 
aided by nine flight controllers who were in nasas mission 
control during apollo 11s historic july 1969 landing the youths 
talked through headsets and completed checklists before giving the 
goahead for the mock landing 
while the 15 students worked in mission control another group of 
children were flying in a simulator at a second challenger 
center in greenbelt md accompanying those children was former 
astronaut michael collins who circled the moon in apollo 11s 
command module while neil armstrong and edwin buzz aldrin landed 
in the lunar module 
i learned what it really feels like and what you have to do to 
