the simulation marked the first time that students from the two 
challenger centers were able to communicate with each other the 
facility in houston was the first center opening in august 1988 
the centers built as a memorial to the seven astronauts who died 
in the explosion of the space shuttle challenger offer youngsters a 
chance to learn by participating in simulated missions the two 
centers are the first of a planned network of simulators 
for about 30 minutes the students sat behind their control 
consoles along with the veteran flight controllers the mostly 
fourth fifth and sixthgraders also watched three television 
monitors above which showed their counterparts working at the other 
