salaam bombay virgin vision english subtitles vhsbeta 
7995 unrated 
 
salaam bombay is a heartrending look at the homeless street 
children of bombay india but its meanings and nuances transcend 
that exotic locale 
the film which won a number of international film awards in 
1988 is a riveting portrayal of how 20th century societies 
including socalled civilized ones are devouring their young 
alternately selling them or selling them short 
producerdirector mira nair traveled the streets of bombay 
fascinated by the resilience of the thousands of children who 
survive by their wits in a squalid world of dirt drugs and 
prostitution she decided to tell their story not with actors but 
with children she gathered from those very backstreets 
salaam bombay is the story of 10yearold krishna abandoned 
first by his mother then by the traveling circus he joins he 
travels to bombay hoping to earn 500 rupees to take back to his 
mother 
krishna acquires street wisdom and a toughness that even leads to 
a murder but somehow almost miraculously he keeps a childlike 
empathy even as he is failing in his own hopes he befriends a 
desperate drug addict and comforts an abject 16yearold sold by 
her own mother to a brothel 
the films producers decided to use proceeds to establish 
learning centers for the street children of bombay and delhi 
salaam bombay is not rated it has no objectionable language 
or sexual encounters but the themes of street life are nonetheless 
unvarnished 
it is a truly exceptional film 
by lee mitgang associated press writer 
</TEXT>
