images om records georganne cassat harp 
 
like some of the larger planets in our solar system marcel 
tourniers images for harp are heavy in atmosphere the music covers 
the gamut of harp effects these short pieces sound a little like 
debussy piano etudes though less complex they were unquestionably 
written by a harpist the liner notes call tournier one of the most 
important harpists and harp composers of the 19th and 20th centuries 
and a judicious one at that we can be thankful he doesnt indulge 
in too many of those sweeping runs such as the kind used as a 
backdrop for movie flashbacks 
these pieces presented here as a whole for the first time are 
fairly simple and pleasant to listen to they have quaint titles 
such as moonlight in a pool replete with rippling run effects 
and children by the christmas crib which nicely evokes the 
choir sound of a christmas carol 
cassat is an accomplished harpist who more often than not avoids 
the sometimes annoying overplucked quality of solo harp 
performances she has an excellent sense of dynamics offering a 
constant interplay of soft and loud passages 
her brief biography oddly points out that she has brought the 
music of the harp to some of the leading royal houses in europe and 
the orient has royalty traditionally been deprived of harp music 
and do those kings and queens feel properly grateful maybe playing 
this disc can make our living rooms feel a bit more regal it 
certainly lends a little atmosphere 
by daniel wakin associated press writer 
</TEXT>
