cycles capitol the doobie brothers 
 
give one of the worlds most popular bands six years off and 
its amazing how many fresh ideas theyll come up with hardly any 
if thats a revelation its the only one shed by cycles the 
doobie brothers first album since 1983 and their first studio 
album since 1980 
five of the six doobies who reunited for cycles were with the 
band when they first hit the top 40 in the early 1970s and much of 
the music here sounds like the doobies of that period that means 
boogie guitars tight harmonies and plenty of percussion 
the music is professionally played but the formula is too 
familiar to generate much excitement and most of the material 
especially the feeble first single the doctor fails to match 
the doobies best songs of the past 
still there are moments of merit guitarist tom johnstons 
wrong number an anticocaine song has a stirring lyric i 
can read your mind offers a lovely vocal counterpoint by patrick 
simmons and could have been an outtake from minute by minute 
perhaps the bands best album 
but cycles sounds used rather than new the guitar riff from 
the doobies chestnut china grove kicks off the doctor the 
riff that opens the oldie listen to the music begins need a 
little taste of love maybe this album shouldve been called 
recycles 
by steven wine associated press writer 
