to be on its best behavior i think roy acuff was especially 
reticent about what was going on he came in when we were doing the 
merle travis sessions we were auditioning for him he told us 
making the new record was more fun than the first time around 
hanna said 
when pop radio stopped playing country rock in the late 1970s 
the nitty gritty dirt band went nashville one of its last pop hits 
was an american dream in 1980 its first country single on 
which ricky scaggs played was long hard road in 1982 
